			THE THREADS CLASS PREPARATION


    ================================================================

   OBTAINING COPIES OF THE "Multithreaded Programming with Pthreads"

  If Bil is not bringing the books himself, they can be ordered from
Prentice Hall at (800) 922-0579, ISBN 0-13-680729-1.  March '00 price is $35
(+ shipping, etc.  Discounts may be available.)  US delivery is about 10
days (rush orders are possible).

    ================================================================

			PRINTING THE STUDENT MANUALS

  For the student manuals (total of ~125 pages + front & back covers) in
order:

cover.ps	This is a single-sided cover page, to be reproduced on
		heavy stock (back blank).
seminar2x1.ps	These ~340 .ps pages are reduced to two .ps pages per
		page side.  They are to be printed doubled-sided (giving four
		.ps pages per printed page) = ~85 pages.
POSIX_code2x1.ps These ~140 .ps pages to be printed doubled-sided
		(giving four .ps pages per printed page) = ~35 pages.
dss.ps		These two pages should be printed doubled-sided on the SAME
		sheet.
marc.ps			ditto
nfs.ps			ditto
photoshop.ps		ditto
uniq.ps			ditto
TAO.ps			ditto

		Blank, heavy stock on the back.
		Bind with wire or spiral binder.

    ================================================================

  If you are making the overhead slides (~500 pages), you will need the
full-sized .ps files (included here). Print seminar.ps and code.ps onto
overhead transparencies.

    ================================================================

broshure3.txt	This is the description of the course.  Not required.

    ================================================================



		INSTALLING AND TESTING THE CLASSROOM PROGRAMS

  Install the files in ./programs_<date>.tar in the students' home
directory:

% cd student1
% tar xf <path>/programs_<date>.tar

Look at ./programs/PThreads/dot_cshrc (it's modified from the SunU classroom
file from Jan '97) and either install that as ~/.cshrc or copy the relevant
portions of it into the .cshrc file you use for students.

o  All machines must be running Solaris 2.6 (or above) with the Solaris
   developer bundle (i.e. all of the include files, etc.)
o  The SPARCworks tools (version 3.1 or above) WITH LICENSES
o  Solaris 2.5: TNFview (http://opcom.sun.ca/toolpages/tnftools.html -- 
   just follow the instructions, it's easy.)
o  Solaris 2.6: TNFview2 (http://www.sun.com/developers/driver/tools/toc.html 
   just follow the instructions, it's easy.)
o  proctool (get it from: http://sunsite.unc.edu/pub/sun-info/mde/proctool/
   just follow the instructions, it's easy.)

After you've gotten these bits together, **PLEASE VERIFY THE INSTALLATION**
by running ./programs/PThreads/test_install.csh.  If that DOESN'T run
correctly, fix it.  There are hints in test_install.csh that may help you
find the problem if it isn't obvious.

